			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">If I dont want the pet to follow me around...
<br />

<br />
I hit guard, then /pet hold. Pet stays in that spot and wont attack anything.
<br />

<br />
Likewise, If I want the pet to follow me, I hit follow, then do /pet hold. Pet follows me all around, but wont attack.
<br />

<br />
Now after you kill a mob, the pet will either go back to the spot you told them to guard, or continue to follow you, depending on what you on what you commanded before the killing.
<br />

<br />
But heres the kicker--- You have to do a /pet hold after having the pet attack... everytime. Its very easy to forget.<br />_________________<br />Morbidor
<br />
67 Necro
<br />
Stromm</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
