			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">There is only one way to turn /pet hold off.  And that is to /pet attack (or /pet kill ... ok fine, two ways) with a valid target which is in range.
<br />

<br />
If the target is illegal (eg. another player or pet) the pet will say so and stay in hold mode.
<br />

<br />
If you have no target, or your target is too far away, your pet will say nothing and will remain in hold mode.
<br />

<br />
/pet guard me or /pet follow (same thing) do not change the hold mode.
<br />
/pet guard here does not change the hold mode
<br />

<br />
Once pet hold is turned off, it stays turned off until you issue another /pet hold command.  ie. your pet will not automatically return to hold mode after killing the mob you just /pet attacked
<br />

<br />
While in hold mode
<br />
- your pet will not attack anything.  
<br />
- Mobs will be added to your pet's hate list as they attack you or your pet.
<br />
- Mobs already on your pet's hate list will not be removed from that hate list if they get mezzed. (they will be removed though if you break the pet hold while they are still mezzed.  The pet will tell you that he is unable to attack that target)
<br />

<br />
/pet back off will clear your pet's hate list.  Even when he is in hold mode. (but mobs will get added to that list again, as they attack you or your pet)
<br />

<br />

<br />
That's about all I can think of on the subject of /pet hold.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
